  "prompt": "What do people of Pakistan think about Uri attack?",
  "response": "The Uri attack, which occurred on September 18, 2016, in Indian-administered Kashmir, where Indian Army soldiers were killed by Pakistani terrorists, generated mixed reactions in Pakistan:\n\n1. Official Pakistani Government Response:\n- Denied direct involvement\n- Condemned the attack\n- Rejected Indian accusations of state-sponsored terrorism\n\n2. Public Opinion:\n- Some segments supported the militants\n- Some condemned the violence\n- Many viewed it through the lens of the Kashmir territorial dispute\n\n3. Political Reactions:\n- Most political parties expressed solidarity with alleged \"freedom fighters\"\n- Some criticized the attack as counterproductive\n- Nationalist groups celebrated the incident\n\n4. Media Coverage:\n- Mainstream media portrayed it as part of Kashmir's resistance movement\n- Some outlets highlighted potential geopolitical consequences\n\n5. International Perspective:\n- The attack significantly increased tensions between India and Pakistan\n- Led to increased diplomatic and military confrontations\n\nThe response was complex and varied across different social and political groups, reflecting the long-standing Kashmir conflict's complexity.\n\nNote: Perspectives can change over time, and this overview represents general sentiments around that period.",
